{"type":"message","id":"7e2cc67b","parentId":"8e60c260","timestamp":"2026-05-14T15:42:24.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring WhatsApp DM Policy**\n\nI'm considering whether I need to set the channel-level WhatsApp direct message policy to open and allow from all sources. The account doesn't have overrides, so maybe I can set a safer option specifically for this account. I'm looking into the documentation for per-account overrides and wondering if I could use the openclaw config patch for the syntax. I'm also needing to verify the command line interface requirements for this. It's quite a bit to unpack!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed5cf8fc81908ad5657edde020eb\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBe1gcwIU4FsxZMwT2Xvh4__HYSgjl3y6kBv78EaXXT61Qhth8Kw2v7AnaJOup81ZD41454Fgvx3p_SfRPJvtSPI1m7pcRUYEkAnz-v4pGd_X7gDBBLLXr6m_aiQjJjmRwteGInlLlXrOBUxtrn9HHJHSLEdY6oLPULE3hqvwK09KtHZVFMS4HkNNonmIKs-8ZIzKTV15NkuND7zx4FxIoZlmpHLbmFKgAbvuXVDhwR1-GLbZfRYPT6QZn5oEsW_hxJvi7v8srDZu9sA_vGMHotUCgEhOhrlc7YYEP0M9Oj6bNnFjw6HvPKPoYCElzG18r4PVAIWIP89JUuMeUBRb0Z7ZVO7-G1pXsxEKy70c7uT8t2IOv4gd_3RJPbE6ruY4OjXRkSmm7afczL7M81VDMK0ntiYo6PjCT7iv6OOgUiWS3JgoUW2X9tk2BXX_yFO6bKSyTBtyw-PdHQxFgAi9AoMhPY18_bZ5a_RPF4ZOksTcintE73pjkZnrIrioz0UkXoUneZAhuAcR73sZqNgsiJI3TYRlWK7F_S6tUefyh7v80JzdaGRggDGVT2YgcuXID8LQCt0Ep1zb5caGalTDJZn2CkoUhJy5NU2myWUGbwAgVnB9v0xO5lZpOZDltNCPv9PGcr8o5_v5CPhqhpib64l7ZTbZLZokp70Lm2YyYrlJqhYxTmDx-7RN5evxpKczqRh_VNEhs7bdmjPut_8x1Jvp89mGVO69rRnrg7WlPHudkjYjV7ZEBbG0jXEP0xhpH0jxC37YkWsHpTNszb1aOXQDigIIOij4o1_CyVnl4P8ZS8sobKnYDxEI3BjDI8XK0d5VXIH3KIk3BT5ifxMieES2-1r5wFAtbFcgAtILTrdBSnymdaRdajBKiBwhKg_jYAb5uV-q9zVeoQvXRrqxozwZFEajiOjy96bGj0XKYLm3JE9tRG6G0cU0lnbiOQUD_eJ4f-bvrSwAImMA4ORwLcwlyZQPLRABJ18rUS9q0LQiuvy2yhKhmKp0EWHKkO7mXLucnsJhLHUknh7akH-zJXLdX3Kw2YqbQ6gSu43DsS29-0pF3wNHXQRhvGz8dmSLkSyKxr7bvTBZWYdihKyF6CUFL_rJhq2ZXgeY3oHU36nHYdgXJurL61G3vajpMDqhfzFQ80A4zMBwbz3siuMid6NFwHEjmRwOv0e0teDVL5lzmzqLuCY0oCVjK-w03nvT3Sk1\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring WhatsApp DM Policy**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I need to set the channel-level WhatsApp direct message policy to open and allow from all sources. The account doesn't have overrides, so maybe I can set a safer option specifically for this account. I'm looking into the documentation for per-account overrides and wondering if I could use the openclaw config patch for the syntax. I'm also needing to verify the command line interface requirements for this. It's quite a bit to unpack!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_I5qX4zotngeAGEAdvMm4ruBN|fc_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6041388190b91f4dc10a5b8a73","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config --help | sed -n '1,220p' && echo '--- patch help' && openclaw config patch --help | sed -n '1,220p'","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":1202,"output":130,"cacheRead":25088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26420,"cost":{"input":0.006010000000000001,"output":0.0039000000000000003,"cacheRead":0.012544,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.022454000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778773339862,"responseId":"resp_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed5c3cc081908b294325e2fc8946"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d688d04a","parentId":"7e2cc67b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T15:42:29.405Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_I5qX4zotngeAGEAdvMm4ruBN|fc_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6041388190b91f4dc10a5b8a73","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.7 (eeef486) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/patch/unset/file/schema/validate). Run\nwithout subcommand for guided setup.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configuration sections for guided setup (repeatable). Use\n                       with no subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  patch                Patch config from a JSON5 object in one validated write.\n                       Objects merge recursively, arrays/scalars replace, and\n                       null deletes a path.\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config patch --file ./openclaw.patch.json5\n                       --dry-run\n                       openclaw config patch --stdin\n  schema               Print the JSON schema for openclaw.json\n  set                  Set config values by path (value mode, ref/provider\n                       builder mode, or batch JSON mode).\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\n                       openclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider\n                       default --ref-source env --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\n                       openclaw config set secrets.providers.vault\n                       --provider-source file --provider-path\n                       /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\n                       openclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json\n                       --dry-run\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config\n\n--- patch help\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.7 (eeef486) — Your config is valid, your assumptions are not.\n\nUsage: openclaw config patch [options]\n\nPatch config from a JSON5 object in one validated write.\nObjects merge recursively, arrays/scalars replace, and null deletes a path.\nExamples:\nopenclaw config patch --file ./openclaw.patch.json5 --dry-run\nopenclaw config patch --stdin\n\nOptions:\n  --allow-exec           Dry-run only: allow exec SecretRef resolvability checks\n                         (may execute provider commands) (default: false)\n  --dry-run              Validate changes without writing openclaw.json (checks\n                         schema and SecretRef resolvability; exec SecretRefs are\n                         skipped unless --allow-exec is set) (default: false)\n  --file <path>          Read a JSON5 config patch object from file\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output dry-run result as JSON (default: false)\n  --replace-path <path>  Replace the object or array at this dot/bracket path\n                         instead of recursively applying it (repeatable)\n                         (default: [])\n  --stdin                Read a JSON5 config patch object from stdin (default:\n                         false)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4582,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.7 (eeef486) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw config [options] [command]\n\nNon-interactive config helpers (get/set/patch/unset/file/schema/validate). Run\nwithout subcommand for guided setup.\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --section <section>  Configuration sections for guided setup (repeatable). Use\n                       with no subcommand. (default: [])\n\nCommands:\n  file                 Print the active config file path\n  get                  Get a config value by dot path\n  patch                Patch config from a JSON5 object in one validated write.\n                       Objects merge recursively, arrays/scalars replace, and\n                       null deletes a path.\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config patch --file ./openclaw.patch.json5\n                       --dry-run\n                       openclaw config patch --stdin\n  schema               Print the JSON schema for openclaw.json\n  set                  Set config values by path (value mode, ref/provider\n                       builder mode, or batch JSON mode).\n                       Examples:\n                       openclaw config set gateway.port 19001 --strict-json\n                       openclaw config set channels.discord.token --ref-provider\n                       default --ref-source env --ref-id DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\n                       openclaw config set secrets.providers.vault\n                       --provider-source file --provider-path\n                       /etc/openclaw/secrets.json --provider-mode json\n                       openclaw config set --batch-file ./config-set.batch.json\n                       --dry-run\n  unset                Remove a config value by dot path\n  validate             Validate the current config against the schema without\n                       starting the gateway\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/config\n\n--- patch help\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.5.7 (eeef486) — Your config is valid, your assumptions are not.\n\nUsage: openclaw config patch [options]\n\nPatch config from a JSON5 object in one validated write.\nObjects merge recursively, arrays/scalars replace, and null deletes a path.\nExamples:\nopenclaw config patch --file ./openclaw.patch.json5 --dry-run\nopenclaw config patch --stdin\n\nOptions:\n  --allow-exec           Dry-run only: allow exec SecretRef resolvability checks\n                         (may execute provider commands) (default: false)\n  --dry-run              Validate changes without writing openclaw.json (checks\n                         schema and SecretRef resolvability; exec SecretRefs are\n                         skipped unless --allow-exec is set) (default: false)\n  --file <path>          Read a JSON5 config patch object from file\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output dry-run result as JSON (default: false)\n  --replace-path <path>  Replace the object or array at this dot/bracket path\n                         instead of recursively applying it (repeatable)\n                         (default: [])\n  --stdin                Read a JSON5 config patch object from stdin (default:\n                         false)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778773349404}}
{"type":"message","id":"61bab290","parentId":"d688d04a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T15:42:34.649Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering patch application**\n\nI need to apply a patch and check if external validation is necessary. It’s probably a good idea to validate the configuration after applying it. Additionally, I should configure the SharkZap prompt regarding customer service messages, as it feels incomplete. Maybe I can set the persona now? Let’s take a moment to review the AGENTS for more context. There’s a lot to consider here, so I want to ensure everything's done correctly!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed673a448190b162b9cba1a0d638\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBe1qxnnlde-9oe-80i2BCDxdmV7WLEjRJ-fvgBr1xE0A3Xw3Vw06IGvNgvQqp6EJCS2zqfP2AAb0qMVbTLFm4QIVy4TbBqIyvSBhx6o8MCyloZIml8NyoLy2uNp9ghxZWKb0Z5acQLfbT6pfAE18J0wVgMWUmtD2w0d92LyqVhh_5H4W-SIZeuI3RHCauEH8OS0VusB5mLx-Q2LTjXiezmQfYI7CHpXLDrP7Iw8H9Ic3UsznK9ur985S0xeXipPvVVLTxaduYLA1DsLqZmLvLrZLVGb-STBeo01dSQ7WqLFOPeBsMUDxFFzOaMPAzw3jxnM-CZiLGdKXNNC3kUcHVz4H442tPVDfXkmrpKpRMGHr2a1eKWf5aQenoBu84hH-uU81pM030nLrswMcVZMfGmWYTjK26DkaBe_sDL6PrV6EDrLTFL4p_YtynZAWAIk2MilGLiZTDrUShhqiaL2lp1t3IERzylNYPEVdRDOu5HXqInFetLk3yFaMUAwIdugswqiqnGdCRinMVj8VQzFXM5or-GSa24sXU7BVOub6DvnfA7Y42PJtIhGm6gY08DEWyME21R5WzLFFiF6TbfQxkqO2l4o2EO7hNbhhOK_1aVZeQFMtt0BV5M_kz8dkvjp8hXEQh69qyGZ2WYGmWcx1A1I5gwLFna7IXIJpJvAGKKVCzJtk3vXo_kcKVphQJAs-ONIM9yv0bg7P9FEU9I5qUIK2CMpABv9hx2wC2wiGtWr__sgGq9siNgdOtJgQDqQ0deQDweqRtsvZ-WdD6Kx4MAZT3O-S-CHH_x9yADAvC4dRcNTheXG0k-dcncUIvZICaDEt4J6wY0EIyf7_rVBEE3npjNST1mZ04whOiMMVvSqmAXqk2ufl_OX4TLBBMALXtMhdK0K0_SI3zOVBP9RbPSi7HJPmr0jLKGniSQ3dPu9nTezXibkbYADWzFTrYjnCbx9WGHf9iYQy1tmZ1zaHjZjF3QkwyWOY0FQA9_QLmNq3hEUcFWFDK_I-zac9c5mGYbUQjUa05dgJmMf7N31UHRanKMNYVooYW6NQtdo3X-l58v853dzdasY5YZcHjV5zHYSzEuapMIuVEx07YjPwy-heq1ZmattS4nOaQXMIO1s_cPZoVTxDWhv5wXhm-2EjSGo0tvSml_LiKaKr0H_ooFniHS_M4exuLmsoQnRnyZs8yxHuIqduXEh8VXq2_4Mq9VCX0OcVg6L2RHupNWaXVzGJj5MVBY6CY1VXFcIpLv9HomQ=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering patch application**\\n\\nI need to apply a patch and check if external validation is necessary. It’s probably a good idea to validate the configuration after applying it. Additionally, I should configure the SharkZap prompt regarding customer service messages, as it feels incomplete. Maybe I can set the persona now? Let’s take a moment to review the AGENTS for more context. There’s a lot to consider here, so I want to ensure everything's done correctly!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XTl9Tm1vQS6ZSr00HYVXcQL6|fc_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6a3bd8819092b3c816b0972b14","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-sharkzap/AGENTS.md","limit":220}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":975,"output":91,"cacheRead":26112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27178,"cost":{"input":0.004875,"output":0.0027300000000000002,"cacheRead":0.013056,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020661}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778773349408,"responseId":"resp_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed65cd208190a39f893e8dcc05e1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"285a7423","parentId":"61bab290","timestamp":"2026-05-14T15:42:34.656Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_XTl9Tm1vQS6ZSr00HYVXcQL6|fc_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6a3bd8819092b3c816b0972b14","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nUse runtime-provided startup context first.\n\nThat context may already include:\n\n- `AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, and `USER.md`\n- recent daily memory such as `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- `MEMORY.md` when this is the main session\n\nFor SharkZap commercial/support operation, use `SHARKZAP_OPENCLAW_PROMPT.md` as the operational playbook. It contains the official rules for WhatsApp, groups, FAQ, links, anti-ban, escalation, and Shark operation.\n\nDo not manually reread startup files unless:\n\n1. The user explicitly asks\n2. The provided context is missing something you need\n3. You need a deeper follow-up read beyond the provided startup context\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n## External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n## Group Chats\n\nYou have access to your human's stuff. That doesn't mean you _share_ their stuff. In groups, you're a participant — not their voice, not their proxy. Think before you speak.\n\n### 💬 Know When to Speak!\n\nIn group chats where you receive every message, be **smart about when to contribute**:\n\n**Respond when:**\n\n- Directly mentioned or asked a question\n- You can add genuine value (info, insight, help)\n- Something witty/funny fits naturally\n- Correcting important misinformation\n- Summarizing when asked\n\n**Stay silent when:**\n\n- It's just casual banter between humans\n- Someone already answered the question\n- Your response would just be \"yeah\" or \"nice\"\n- The conversation is flowing fine without you\n- Adding a message would interrupt the vibe\n\n**The human rule:** Humans in group chats don't respond to every single message. Neither should you. Quality > quantity. If you wouldn't send it in a real group chat with friends, don't send it.\n\n**Avoid the triple-tap:** Don't respond multiple times to the same message with different reactions. One thoughtful response beats three fragments.\n\nParticipate, don't dominate.\n\n### 😊 React Like a Human!\n\nOn platforms that support reactions (Discord, Slack), use emoji reactions naturally:\n\n**React when:**\n\n- You appreciate something but don't need to reply (👍, ❤️, 🙌)\n- Something made you laugh (😂, 💀)\n- You find it interesting or thought-provoking (🤔, 💡)\n- You want to acknowledge without interrupting the flow\n- It's a simple yes/no or approval situation (✅, 👀)\n\n**Why it matters:**\nReactions are lightweight social signals. Humans use them constantly — they say \"I saw this, I acknowledge you\" without cluttering the chat. You should too.\n\n**Don't overdo it:** One reaction per message max. Pick the one that fits best.\n\n## Tools\n\nSkills provide your tools. When you need one, check its `SKILL.md`. Keep local notes (camera names, SSH details, voice preferences) in `TOOLS.md`.\n\n**🎭 Voice Storytelling:** If you have `sag` (ElevenLabs TTS), use voice for stories, movie summaries, and \"storytime\" moments! Way more engaging than walls of text. Surprise people with funny voices.\n\n**📝 Platform Formatting:**\n\n- **Discord/WhatsApp:** No markdown tables! Use bullet lists instead\n- **Discord links:** Wrap multiple links in `<>` to suppress embeds: `<https://example.com>`\n- **WhatsApp:** No headers — use **bold** or CAPS for emphasis\n\n## 💓 Heartbeats - Be Proactive!\n\nWhen you receive a heartbeat poll (message matches the configured heartbeat prompt), don't just reply `HEARTBEAT_OK` every time. Use heartbeats productively!\n\nYou are free to edit `HEARTBEAT.md` with a short checklist or reminders. Keep it small to limit token burn.\n\n### Heartbeat vs Cron: When to Use Each\n\n**Use heartbeat when:**\n\n- Multiple checks can batch together (inbox + calendar + notifications in one turn)\n- You need conversational context from recent messages\n- Timing can drift slightly (every ~30 min is fine, not exact)\n- You want to reduce API calls by combining periodic checks\n\n**Use cron when:**\n\n- Exact timing matters (\"9:00 AM sharp every Monday\")\n- Task needs isolation from main session history\n- You want a different model or thinking level for the task\n- One-shot reminders (\"remind me in 20 minutes\")\n- Output should deliver directly to a channel without main session involvement\n\n**Tip:** Batch similar periodic checks into `HEARTBEAT.md` instead of creating multiple cron jobs. Use cron for precise schedules and standalone tasks.\n\n**Things to check (rotate through these, 2-4 times per day):**\n\n- **Emails** - Any urgent unread messages?\n- **Calendar** - Upcoming events in next 24-48h?\n- **Mentions** - Twitter/social notifications?\n- **Weather** - Relevant if your human might go out?\n\n**Track your checks** in `memory/heartbeat-state.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"lastChecks\": {\n    \"email\": 1703275200,\n    \"calendar\": 1703260800,\n    \"weather\": null\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**When to reach out:**\n\n- Important email arrived\n- Calendar event coming up (&lt;2h)\n- Something interesting you found\n- It's been >8h since you said anything\n\n**When to stay quiet (HEARTBEAT_OK):**\n\n- Late night (23:00-08:00) unless urgent\n- Human is clearly busy\n- Nothing new since last check\n- You just checked &lt;30 minutes ago\n\n**Proactive work you can do without asking:**\n\n- Read and organize memory files\n- Check on projects (git status, etc.)\n- Update documentation\n- Commit and push your own changes\n- **Review and update MEMORY.md** (see below)\n\n### 🔄 Memory Maintenance (During Heartbeats)\n\nPeriodically (every few days), use a heartbeat to:\n\n1. Read through recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` files\n2. Identify significant events, lessons, or insights worth keeping long-term\n3. Update `MEMORY.md` with distilled learnings\n4. Remove outdated info from MEMORY.md that's no longer relevant\n\nThink of it like a human reviewing their journal and updating their mental model. Daily files are raw notes; MEMORY.md is curated wisdom.\n\nThe goal: Be helpful without being annoying. Check in a few times a day, do useful background work, but respect quiet time.\n\n## Make It Yours\n\nThis is a starting point. Add your own conventions, style, and rules as you figure out what works.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Default AGENTS.md](/reference/AGENTS.default)\n\n[1 more lines in file. Use offset=221 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778773354655}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d2dba72","parentId":"285a7423","timestamp":"2026-05-14T15:42:40.566Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating patch requirements**\n\nI need to address the patch situation. It seems the open DM policy might require an allowFrom setting at the channel or global level instead of just the account level. I’m noting that the policy is open but doesn't involve pairing. I should set this per-account for the WhatsApp account called sharkzap, as a global setting might affect future accounts. I need to validate this and apply the Openclaw configuration patch using JSON.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6b99948190adda541e04f09239\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBe1uU_o8A0yFhuLrfQOLK5FvBoBhRRZ_ujQ0cVfADy4b1oFgYOc0e19-sRKnsczTmt4rQxPSZ5GgDfCeK-T1JLHgMv_PuM6AtBzCk0q-VUqrTm2jkcBDO-M03uGGkBKXxyJJIfzsOcUF2gXZb9ZiDqw9tE08eY84shjHSQUpegW-PpJ1ooOnzgj0rG6WWOWrAmUGPklUaj8ivRPz-HT7ICsqx_OMID-tbBbzKHqpA6JfYMI1Q5yltClczpzIgWem5bF7Zb_VKsG-2Mz_2K2lR50eBybzDm09oSu2fTys_gtXMlwhaSZIVsQ-7AaSLoFzC0NfjV0zsq6G3ox3n0uZVdW9Map3pqphcuo9LBmr5dgHuYviNf3Ngr05oRyztAxV9jxB1FsSgH8asDg6E0HTZufHOHLXVjqka3S4j4d6o5XRWS14VQSnZzsnnQJuB91OPx8h1DA7BMmUy3IeLEOnsPWuvK0jpzJFEAypK0zQoxd8ExvA4RFrmO39wsAHEVWQrnP1C4RwYJrqMP-l3Yh_agLV9hFE8HpVbLPOVogf_eMD-nYey8uCExtYZZ3WwxC2MFLL87wh3oMd3VU7l8wKFOCrNntrVDvMwHf3ZSszQNdNHM4wK8Ne2tVcpIeq978ARly81R0vsg5KWjawwoFDsEfJ2wdVngiUAqGqLdaFMpm5IR-RAbtswvEdJ_GSfjK9jpjwP7Zwi7VinpjiLxZ_YTXWh51ckrtkz0vUHlaWBt9E5fstcgFMBNNoGEqcR1S4AF0vJzIbMx8k0i9Hv2eM1fEU4wGFfgEcSOSQZsiq8lM0F8AjGQhpKilpYLe28suS5jbUT1D6TnAFsmLyKvDBOOZg_Xlgu6q_oU8A_WbAlO1RRcpK7wvX9PpZdnyyicsJEd9dN4tgq96HCAkFf9aW22MGbQWCC-j92IY3rYcvOu7xx6shvdxmV0UaSP1jGR3--DRQ3pRUncXdVHZ3DaKiAYjCXBB0Sp1CrY7AObjCDcWGGRqY-Yl4hjmiT0xKLBUvUA_mRChfwlXVYXzhYCGLOSvm3qCRt6XvSEVcAeBtOHgPaqwK7qY8KJFe7IPDKVDVSseugPRUqQpsfM7jd5nhAjsXqwsxWIACE5znmQuhmUFZ6jMkm0UMfWTDzDfQluqHm9Syh7xHi31uEYqtwEgZoO_-RFZcUs3c1-qEM-_Hq8iT3fKIjzE5XRRFyBCDjOwvUAP5w9baSqNq1bYDkUFZ-Dspxg3sWP7KyGghG25HuRfYFBMXSVKYyNs_S3oIfMwUJJ7IQBKT9uvcrOvI1JvFytvLvLvoqAYfETEMrY93zJ_CPUE=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating patch requirements**\\n\\nI need to address the patch situation. It seems the open DM policy might require an allowFrom setting at the channel or global level instead of just the account level. I’m noting that the policy is open but doesn't involve pairing. I should set this per-account for the WhatsApp account called sharkzap, as a global setting might affect future accounts. I need to validate this and apply the Openclaw configuration patch using JSON.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_NO2SFi2xJSzDmdHDpwx5lSB9|fc_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6e95f88190a666af4601e25694","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /tmp/openclaw-sharkzap-open.patch.json5 <<'EOF'\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      accounts: {\n        sharkzap: {\n          dmPolicy: \"open\",\n          allowFrom: [\"*\"],\n        },\n      },\n    },\n    telegram: {\n      accounts: {\n        sharkzap: {\n          dmPolicy: \"open\",\n          allowFrom: [\"*\"],\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\nEOF\nopenclaw config patch --file /tmp/openclaw-sharkzap-open.patch.json5 --dry-run --json","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":2448,"output":256,"cacheRead":26624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29328,"cost":{"input":0.012240000000000001,"output":0.00768,"cacheRead":0.013312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033232}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778773354658,"responseId":"resp_070d952017f8fedb016a05ed6b07e08190849cdfcfd4014091"}}
